headline: HousingIQ forecasts 21.1% increase in US house prices over next twelve months.
us_overview: US house price appreciation is forecasted to increase to 21.1% over the next twelve months from the current 14.3% appreciation rate as gauged by the Housing Market Vitality Indicator (HMVI).
us_overview_2: At the state level, 51 of the 50 states and D.C. are trending up and 18 are outperforming the national market. 97% of the 402 metro markets are trending up and 164 are outperforming the overall U.S. market.

overview: In 38 states, house price appreciation is expected to be lower than the national market. Zero state that currently underperform the national market, is anticipated to improve and outperform the national market.

metro_overview: The top 5 major metro markets have a median forecasted appreciation rate of 32.6% compared to the bottom 5's median forecasted rate of 10.1%.

overview: 70% of the metro markets are expected to underperform the national market. 9, currently underperforming metro markets are anticipated to improve and outperform the national market over the next twelve months.
